// Topological sorting to find the longest path length in the DAG
class Solution {
int m, n;
public:
vector<vector<int>> minScore(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
m = grid.size(), n = grid[0].size();
unordered_map<int, vector<int>> mapping; // <cell val, coordinate>
unordered_map<int, vector<int>> graph;
unordered_map<int, int> indegree;
for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
mapping[grid[i][j]] = {i, j};
indegree[grid[i][j]] = 0;
}
}
for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
vector<int> row(grid[i]);
sort(row.begin(), row.end());
for (int j = 0; j < n - 1; j++) {
graph[row[j]].push_back(row[j + 1]);
indegree[row[j + 1]]++;
}
}
for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
vector<int> col;
for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
col.push_back(grid[i][j]);
}
sort(col.begin(), col.end());
for (int i = 0; i < m - 1; i++) {
graph[col[i]].push_back(col[i + 1]);
indegree[col[i + 1]]++;
}
}
// topological sort to find the longest path length
queue<int> que;
for(auto it = indegree.begin(); it != indegree.end(); it++) {
if(it->second == 0) {
que.push(it->first);
}
}
int level = 0;
while (!que.empty()) {
level++;
int levelSize = que.size();
while(levelSize--) {
int u = que.front(); que.pop();
grid[mapping[u][0]][mapping[u][1]] = level;
for(auto v : graph[u]) {
indegree[v]--;
if(indegree[v] == 0) {
que.push(v);
}
}
}
}
return grid;
}
};
